Date: Fri, 3 Mar 2000 11:09 GMTFrom: "Simon Bell" <simple@dial.pipex.com> Subject: Re: audio decoder API?To: "Steve Weyer" <sweyer@bellatlantic.net> Hi Steve,The body of an audio message should contain the following slots: {class: 'audio,|MIME:Simple|: { codec: '|WAV:Simple|, info: "WAV Audio" }, title: "Sample sound",data: <binary>}codec is a symbol for the decoder, valid values are: '|AIFF:Simple|'|WAV:Simple|'|uLaw:Simple|'|GSM:Simple|info is a string displayed in the message's info slip. data is the sound data in the appropriate format, AIFF/WAV/etc. The audio decoder generates a Newton sound frame from this each timethe stationery is opened and plays that.Simon